<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1694] Query#mergeBooleanQueries argument should be of type BooleanQuery[] instead of Query[]</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1694</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;The method #mergeBooleanQueries accepts Query[] and casts elements to BooleanQuery without checking. This will guarantee a ClassCastException if it is not a boolean query. We should enforce this by changing the signature. This won&apos;t really break back compat. as it only works with instances of BooleanQuery.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
