                    <comment id="12720139" author="mikemccand" created="Tue, 16 Jun 2009 15:06:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good, thanks Simon.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Technically it&apos;s a break in jar drop-in ability back compat, since the method signature has changed.  However, I think it&apos;s unlikely apps are using this rather expert API, and we already don&apos;t have jar drop-in ability for 2.9 anyway, and as you said if you attempt to pass a non-BooleanQuery, you&apos;ll hit a cast exception anwyay.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I plan to commit shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
